        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 2.—Dorsal (top left) and ventral (top right) views, with cranium and mandible shown in left lateral view (bottom) of a skull of an adult (gender unknown) Myrmecophaga tridactyla (UTCM [University of Tennessee at Chattanooga Natural History Museum] 1590), commercially obtained specimen lacking locality data. Occipitonasal length is 351.4 mm. Illustration by Julia Morgan Scott used with permission." ;
